   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Preprocesamiento de Audio para Análisis Paralingüístico\n",
    "\n",
    "Objetivo: limpiar y normalizar el audio de una llamada telefónica antes de correr\n",
    "la diarización y la extracción de features, para maximizar la calidad de las estimaciones.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Problemas típicos en audio de llamadas\n",
    "\n",
    "| Problema | Efecto en los features | Solución |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Ruido de fondo (oficina, calle) | Jitter/HNR erróneos, pitch inestable | Reducción espectral de ruido |\n",
    "| Códec telefónico (banda estrecha 300–3400 Hz) | F0 estimable, pero armónicos cortados | Bandpass + pre-énfasis |\n",
    "| Niveles dispares entre hablantes | Un hablante domina la energía | Normalización de loudness (LUFS) |\n",
    "| DC offset | Distorsión en RMS y ZCR | Eliminación del offset |\n",
    "| Clipping (saturación) | Jitter/Shimmer artificialmente altos | Detección y suavizado de clips |\n",
    "| Silencio excesivo | Dilución de la línea base | VAD (detección de actividad vocal) |\n",
    "| Eco / reverberación | Pitch doble, energía aumentada artificialmente | Filtro de cancelación de eco |\n",
    "\n",
    "## Orden de aplicación\n",
    "```\n",
    "Raw audio\n",
    "  1. Convertir a mono / 16 kHz\n",
    "  2. Eliminar DC offset\n",
    "  3. Detectar y reparar clipping\n",
    "  4. Reducción de ruido (spectral gating)\n",
    "  5. Filtro bandpass (300–3400 Hz)\n",
    "  6. Pre-énfasis (realza armónicos altos)\n",
    "  7. Normalización de loudness (LUFS objetivo)\n",
    "  8. VAD — recortar silencios largos\n",
    "  → Audio limpio para diarización y features\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# %pip install librosa soundfile pydub noisereduce pyloudnorm scipy numpy matplotlib"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import librosa\n",
    "import librosa.display\n",
    "import soundfile as sf\n",
    "import noisereduce as nr\n",
    "import pyloudnorm as pyln\n",
    "from scipy.signal import butter, sosfiltfilt, find_peaks\n",
    "from scipy.ndimage import uniform_filter1d\n",
    "from pydub import AudioSegment\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 100\n",
    "OUTPUT = Path('output_preprocessing')\n",
    "OUTPUT.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "print('OK')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Configuración"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── Entrada / salida ─────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "# Puedes apuntar a tu propio archivo, o usar el WAV sintético del experimento\n",
    "INPUT_AUDIO  = 'output_experiments/llamada_sintetica.wav'\n",
    "OUTPUT_AUDIO = OUTPUT / 'llamada_clean.wav'\n",
    "\n",
    "TARGET_SR    = 16_000   # Hz — requerido por pyannote y óptimo para voz\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── Parámetros de cada etapa ─────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bandpass: frecuencias de corte (Hz)\n",
    "BP_LOW   = 300    # < 300 Hz → zumbidos, ruido de red eléctrica\n",
    "BP_HIGH  = 3400   # > 3400 Hz → silbidos, ruido de alta frecuencia\n",
    "# Nota: telefonía GSM usa 300–3400 Hz; para audio de alta calidad puedes subir a 8000 Hz\n",
    "\n",
    "# Pre-énfasis: realza frecuencias altas para compensar la caída natural de la voz\n",
    "PREEMPH_COEF = 0.97   # rango típico: 0.90 – 0.99\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loudness objetivo (LUFS — Loudness Units relative to Full Scale)\n",
    "# -23 LUFS es el estándar broadcast; -16 LUFS es más adecuado para análisis\n",
    "TARGET_LUFS = -16.0\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clipping: umbral para detectar saturación\n",
    "CLIP_THRESHOLD = 0.98   # muestras con |y| > threshold se consideran clipeadas\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reducción de ruido: proporción del espectro de ruido a sustraer\n",
    "# 1.0 = sustrae exactamente el perfil de ruido; > 1.0 más agresivo\n",
    "NOISE_REDUCTION_PROP = 1.0\n",
    "# Duración (en segundos) del fragmento inicial que asumimos como \"solo ruido\"\n",
    "# para estimar el perfil de ruido\n",
    "NOISE_PROFILE_S = 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "# VAD: silencio mínimo para recortar (segundos)\n",
    "VAD_MIN_SILENCE_S  = 0.5   # silencios más cortos se mantienen (pausas naturales)\n",
    "VAD_ENERGY_THRESH  = 0.01  # fracción de la energía máxima bajo la cual = silencio\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Configuración cargada.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Carga y diagnóstico inicial\n",
    "\n",
    "Antes de procesar, inspeccionamos el audio crudo para entender qué problemas tiene."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def load_raw(path: str, target_sr: int):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Carga audio a mono/target_sr.\"\"\"\n",
    "    audio = AudioSegment.from_file(path)\n",
    "    audio = audio.set_channels(1).set_frame_rate(target_sr)\n",
    "    tmp = str(OUTPUT / '_raw_mono.wav')\n",
    "    audio.export(tmp, format='wav')\n",
    "    y, sr = librosa.load(tmp, sr=target_sr, mono=True)\n",
    "    return y.astype(np.float32), sr\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def diagnose(y: np.ndarray, sr: int, label: str = 'Audio') -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calcula métricas de calidad del audio y las imprime.\"\"\"\n",
    "    duration   = len(y) / sr\n",
    "    rms        = np.sqrt(np.mean(y**2))\n",
    "    peak       = np.abs(y).max()\n",
    "    crest_db   = 20 * np.log10(peak / (rms + 1e-9))\n",
    "    dc_offset  = np.mean(y)\n",
    "    clip_pct   = (np.abs(y) > CLIP_THRESHOLD).mean() * 100\n",
    "    silence_pct= (np.abs(y) < VAD_ENERGY_THRESH * peak).mean() * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "    # SNR aproximado: energía de frames con voz vs. sin voz\n",
    "    frame_rms  = librosa.feature.rms(y=y, frame_length=512, hop_length=256)[0]\n",
    "    thr        = frame_rms.mean() * 0.5\n",
    "    voice_rms  = frame_rms[frame_rms > thr].mean() if (frame_rms > thr).any() else np.nan\n",
    "    noise_rms  = frame_rms[frame_rms <= thr].mean() if (frame_rms <= thr).any() else np.nan\n",
    "    snr_db     = 20 * np.log10(voice_rms / (noise_rms + 1e-9)) if noise_rms else np.nan\n",
    "\n",
    "    stats = dict(\n",
    "        duration_s  = round(duration, 2),\n",
    "        rms         = round(float(rms), 5),\n",
    "        peak        = round(float(peak), 4),\n",
    "        crest_db    = round(float(crest_db), 1),\n",
    "        dc_offset   = round(float(dc_offset), 6),\n",
    "        clip_pct    = round(float(clip_pct), 3),\n",
    "        silence_pct = round(float(silence_pct), 1),\n",
    "        snr_db_est  = round(float(snr_db), 1) if np.isfinite(snr_db) else 'N/A',\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'\\n── {label} ──────────────────────')\n",
    "    for k, v in stats.items():\n",
    "        flag = ''\n",
    "        if k == 'dc_offset'    and abs(v) > 0.01:  flag = '  ⚠ DC offset alto'\n",
    "        if k == 'clip_pct'     and v > 0.5:        flag = '  ⚠ clipping detectado'\n",
    "        if k == 'silence_pct'  and v > 40:         flag = '  ⚠ mucho silencio'\n",
    "        if k == 'snr_db_est'   and isinstance(v, float) and v < 15: flag = '  ⚠ SNR bajo'\n",
    "        print(f'  {k:<18}: {v}{flag}')\n",
    "    return stats\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_raw, SR = load_raw(INPUT_AUDIO, TARGET_SR)\n",
    "stats_raw = diagnose(y_raw, SR, 'Audio crudo')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Visualización diagnóstica inicial"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_diagnostic(y: np.ndarray, sr: int, title: str, save_name: str = None):\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 10))\n",
    "    gs  = gridspec.GridSpec(3, 2, figure=fig, hspace=0.45, wspace=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "    t = np.linspace(0, len(y) / sr, len(y))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Forma de onda\n",
    "    ax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0, :])\n",
    "    ax1.plot(t, y, color='steelblue', linewidth=0.4)\n",
    "    ax1.axhline( CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.7, label='Clip threshold')\n",
    "    ax1.axhline(-CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "    ax1.set_title(f'Forma de onda — {title}')\n",
    "    ax1.set_ylabel('Amplitud')\n",
    "    ax1.set_xlabel('Tiempo (s)')\n",
    "    ax1.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Espectrograma\n",
    "    ax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 0])\n",
    "    S   = librosa.amplitude_to_db(np.abs(librosa.stft(y)), ref=np.max)\n",
    "    librosa.display.specshow(S, sr=sr, x_axis='time', y_axis='hz', ax=ax2, cmap='magma')\n",
    "    ax2.set_ylim(0, 4000)\n",
    "    ax2.axhline(BP_LOW,  color='cyan',  linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8, label=f'BP {BP_LOW} Hz')\n",
    "    ax2.axhline(BP_HIGH, color='lime',  linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2, alpha=0.8, label=f'BP {BP_HIGH} Hz')\n",
    "    ax2.set_title('Espectrograma (0–4 kHz)')\n",
    "    ax2.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Distribución de amplitudes (histograma)\n",
    "    ax3 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1, 1])\n",
    "    ax3.hist(y, bins=200, color='steelblue', alpha=0.75, density=True)\n",
    "    ax3.axvline( CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5, label='Clip')\n",
    "    ax3.axvline(-CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "    ax3.axvline(np.mean(y), color='orange', linestyle='-', linewidth=1.5, label=f'DC={np.mean(y):.4f}')\n",
    "    ax3.set_title('Distribución de amplitudes')\n",
    "    ax3.set_xlabel('Amplitud')\n",
    "    ax3.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Energía RMS por frame\n",
    "    ax4 = fig.add_subplot(gs[2, 0])\n",
    "    rms  = librosa.feature.rms(y=y, frame_length=512, hop_length=256)[0]\n",
    "    t_rms = librosa.frames_to_time(np.arange(len(rms)), sr=sr, hop_length=256)\n",
    "    ax4.fill_between(t_rms, librosa.amplitude_to_db(rms, ref=np.max), alpha=0.7, color='darkorange')\n",
    "    ax4.axhline(librosa.amplitude_to_db(np.array([rms.mean() * 0.5]), ref=np.max)[0],\n",
    "                color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2, label='VAD threshold')\n",
    "    ax4.set_title('Energía RMS por frame')\n",
    "    ax4.set_ylabel('dB')\n",
    "    ax4.set_xlabel('Tiempo (s)')\n",
    "    ax4.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Espectro promedio\n",
    "    ax5 = fig.add_subplot(gs[2, 1])\n",
    "    freqs = np.fft.rfftfreq(2048, d=1/sr)\n",
    "    mag   = np.abs(np.fft.rfft(y, n=2048))\n",
    "    mag_db = 20 * np.log10(mag + 1e-9)\n",
    "    ax5.plot(freqs, mag_db, color='purple', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "    ax5.axvline(BP_LOW,  color='cyan', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2)\n",
    "    ax5.axvline(BP_HIGH, color='lime', linestyle='--', linewidth=1.2)\n",
    "    ax5.set_xlim(0, sr // 2)\n",
    "    ax5.set_title('Espectro de amplitud promedio')\n",
    "    ax5.set_xlabel('Frecuencia (Hz)')\n",
    "    ax5.set_ylabel('dB')\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.suptitle(f'Diagnóstico — {title}', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    if save_name:\n",
    "        plt.savefig(OUTPUT / save_name, dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
