    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_diagnostic(y_raw, SR, 'Audio crudo', 'diag_raw.png')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Pipeline de preprocesamiento\n",
    "\n",
    "Cada etapa es una función pura: recibe `y` y devuelve `y` transformado.\n",
    "Así es fácil activar/desactivar pasos individualmente."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.1 DC offset — eliminación del desplazamiento de continua\n",
    "\n",
    "El DC offset es una componente DC constante que desplaza la señal del cero.\n",
    "Aparece en hardware de grabación de baja calidad o compresores de audio.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Efecto si no se elimina**: RMS inflado artificialmente, ZCR reducido."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def remove_dc_offset(y: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Resta la media de la señal para centrarla en cero.\"\"\"\n",
    "    offset = np.mean(y)\n",
    "    y_out  = y - offset\n",
    "    print(f'DC offset eliminado: {offset:.6f} → {np.mean(y_out):.2e}')\n",
    "    return y_out.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_dc = remove_dc_offset(y_raw)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.2 Detección y reparación de clipping\n",
    "\n",
    "El clipping ocurre cuando la señal satura el conversor A/D: las muestras quedan\n",
    "truncadas en ±1.0 (o el valor máximo del formato). Genera armónicos artificiales\n",
    "que disparatan el jitter y el shimmer.\n",
    "\n",
    "Estrategia: detectar runs de muestras consecutivas cerca del límite\n",
    "e interpolar con una spline cúbica."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def repair_clipping(y: np.ndarray, threshold: float = 0.98) -> tuple:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Detecta samples saturados (|y| >= threshold) e interpola.\n",
    "    Devuelve (y_reparado, máscara_de_clips).\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    from scipy.interpolate import CubicSpline\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_out     = y.copy()\n",
    "    clip_mask = np.abs(y) >= threshold\n",
    "    n_clips   = clip_mask.sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "    if n_clips == 0:\n",
    "        print('Sin clipping detectado.')\n",
    "        return y_out, clip_mask\n",
    "\n",
    "    clip_pct = n_clips / len(y) * 100\n",
    "    print(f'Clipping detectado: {n_clips} muestras ({clip_pct:.3f}%)')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Interpolar: usar muestras no clipeadas como puntos de control\n",
    "    idx_all  = np.arange(len(y))\n",
    "    idx_good = idx_all[~clip_mask]\n",
    "    idx_bad  = idx_all[ clip_mask]\n",
    "\n",
    "    if len(idx_good) < 4:\n",
    "        print('  Muy pocas muestras buenas para interpolar — se devuelve sin cambios.')\n",
    "        return y_out, clip_mask\n",
    "\n",
    "    cs = CubicSpline(idx_good, y[idx_good])\n",
    "    y_out[idx_bad] = np.clip(cs(idx_bad), -threshold, threshold)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'  Reparadas: {n_clips} muestras interpoladas.')\n",
    "    return y_out.astype(np.float32), clip_mask\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_clip, clip_mask = repair_clipping(y_dc, CLIP_THRESHOLD)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualizar zonas clipeadas\n",
    "if clip_mask.any():\n",
    "    t_ax = np.linspace(0, len(y_raw) / SR, len(y_raw))\n",
    "    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(16, 5), sharex=True)\n",
    "    for ax, (y_v, lbl) in zip(axes, [(y_dc, 'Antes'), (y_clip, 'Después')]):\n",
    "        ax.plot(t_ax, y_v, linewidth=0.4, color='steelblue')\n",
    "        ax.fill_between(t_ax, -1, 1, where=clip_mask, color='red', alpha=0.3,\n",
    "                         label='Zona clipeada')\n",
    "        ax.axhline( CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "        ax.axhline(-CLIP_THRESHOLD, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "        ax.set_ylabel(lbl)\n",
    "    axes[0].legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "    axes[1].set_xlabel('Tiempo (s)')\n",
    "    plt.suptitle('Reparación de clipping', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(OUTPUT / 'clipping_repair.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.3 Reducción de ruido (Spectral Gating)\n",
    "\n",
    "El método de **spectral gating** (o sustracción espectral estadística):\n",
    "1. Estima el perfil de ruido a partir de un fragmento sin voz (inicio del audio)\n",
    "2. Para cada frame, si la magnitud espectral está cerca del perfil de ruido → se atenúa\n",
    "3. Si supera el perfil → se preserva (es señal de voz)\n",
    "\n",
    "Usamos `noisereduce` que implementa esto de forma robusta con un umbral suave.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Cuidado**: reducción demasiado agresiva genera \"musical noise\" (artefactos metálicos)\n",
    "> que distorsiona jitter/shimmer. Usamos `prop_decrease=1.0` que es conservador."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def reduce_noise(y: np.ndarray, sr: int,\n",
    "                 noise_profile_s: float = 0.5,\n",
    "                 prop_decrease: float = 1.0) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Estima el ruido de los primeros `noise_profile_s` segundos\n",
    "    y aplica spectral gating a toda la señal.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    n_noise = int(noise_profile_s * sr)\n",
    "    noise_clip = y[:n_noise]\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_clean = nr.reduce_noise(\n",
    "        y              = y,\n",
    "        sr             = sr,\n",
    "        y_noise        = noise_clip,\n",
    "        prop_decrease  = prop_decrease,\n",
    "        stationary     = False,    # ruido no estacionario (cambia con el tiempo)\n",
    "        n_fft          = 1024,\n",
    "        win_length     = 1024,\n",
    "        hop_length     = 256,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Calcular SNR antes/después (estimación)\n",
    "    snr_before = 20 * np.log10(np.sqrt(np.mean(y**2)) / (np.sqrt(np.mean(noise_clip**2)) + 1e-9))\n",
    "    noise_after = y_clean[:n_noise]\n",
    "    snr_after  = 20 * np.log10(np.sqrt(np.mean(y_clean**2)) / (np.sqrt(np.mean(noise_after**2)) + 1e-9))\n",
    "    print(f'Reducción de ruido: SNR estimado {snr_before:.1f} dB → {snr_after:.1f} dB')\n",
    "\n",
    "    return y_clean.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_nr = reduce_noise(y_clip, SR, NOISE_PROFILE_S, NOISE_REDUCTION_PROP)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Comparar espectros antes/después\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "for ax, (y_v, lbl) in zip(axes, [(y_clip, 'Antes'), (y_nr, 'Después')]):\n",
    "    S = librosa.amplitude_to_db(np.abs(librosa.stft(y_v)), ref=np.max)\n",
    "    librosa.display.specshow(S, sr=SR, x_axis='time', y_axis='hz', ax=ax, cmap='magma')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim(0, 4000)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'Reducción de ruido — {lbl}')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(OUTPUT / 'noise_reduction.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.4 Filtro bandpass\n",
    "\n",
    "Corta las frecuencias fuera del rango de la voz telefónica (300–3400 Hz):\n",
    "- **< 300 Hz**: ruido de HVAC, vibración mecánica, interferencia de red eléctrica (50/60 Hz)\n",
    "- **> 3400 Hz**: ruido de alta frecuencia, aliasing del códec\n",
    "\n",
    "Usamos un filtro Butterworth de orden 5 aplicado con `sosfiltfilt`\n",
    "(filtrado en doble pasada, fase cero → no desplaza el pitch)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def bandpass_filter(y: np.ndarray, sr: int,\n",
    "                    low_hz: float = 300, high_hz: float = 3400,\n",
    "                    order: int = 5) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Filtro pasa-banda Butterworth de doble pasada (fase cero).\n",
    "    No introduce retardo de fase → las estimaciones de pitch no se ven afectadas.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    nyq  = sr / 2\n",
    "    sos  = butter(order, [low_hz / nyq, high_hz / nyq], btype='band', output='sos')\n",
    "    y_out = sosfiltfilt(sos, y)\n",
    "    print(f'Bandpass aplicado: {low_hz}–{high_hz} Hz  (orden {order}, fase cero)')\n",
    "    return y_out.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_bp = bandpass_filter(y_nr, SR, BP_LOW, BP_HIGH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualizar la respuesta en frecuencia del filtro\n",
    "from scipy.signal import sosfreqz\n",
    "nyq = SR / 2\n",
    "sos_viz = butter(5, [BP_LOW / nyq, BP_HIGH / nyq], btype='band', output='sos')\n",
    "w, h    = sosfreqz(sos_viz, worN=4096, fs=SR)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "ax.plot(w, 20 * np.log10(np.abs(h) + 1e-9), color='navy', linewidth=2)\n",
    "ax.axvline(BP_LOW,  color='red',   linestyle='--', label=f'{BP_LOW} Hz')\n",
    "ax.axvline(BP_HIGH, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'{BP_HIGH} Hz')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, SR // 2)\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(-80, 5)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Frecuencia (Hz)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Magnitud (dB)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Respuesta en frecuencia — Filtro bandpass')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(OUTPUT / 'bandpass_response.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.5 Pre-énfasis\n",
    "\n",
    "La voz humana tiene una caída natural de ~6 dB/octava en las frecuencias altas.\n",
    "El pre-énfasis compensa esto con un filtro de primer orden:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$y[n] = x[n] - \\alpha \\cdot x[n-1]$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Con α = 0.97 se realzan las frecuencias > 1 kHz, lo que mejora:\n",
    "- La estimación de formantes (tracto vocal)\n",
    "- La estabilidad del pitch estimado con pyin\n",
    "- La separabilidad de fricativas y vocales en el espectro"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pre_emphasis(y: np.ndarray, coef: float = 0.97) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Filtro de pre-énfasis: y[n] = x[n] - coef * x[n-1]\n",
    "    coef típico: 0.95 – 0.99\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    y_out = np.append(y[0], y[1:] - coef * y[:-1])\n",
    "    print(f'Pre-énfasis aplicado: α={coef}')\n",
    "    return y_out.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_pe = pre_emphasis(y_bp, PREEMPH_COEF)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Comparar espectros\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 4))\n",
    "freqs = np.fft.rfftfreq(len(y_bp), d=1/SR)\n",
    "mag_before = 20 * np.log10(np.abs(np.fft.rfft(y_bp)) + 1e-9)\n",
    "mag_after  = 20 * np.log10(np.abs(np.fft.rfft(y_pe)) + 1e-9)\n",
    "ax.plot(freqs, mag_before, color='steelblue', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.7, label='Antes')\n",
    "ax.plot(freqs, mag_after,  color='darkorange', linewidth=0.8, alpha=0.7, label='Después (pre-énfasis)')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(0, 4000)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Frecuencia (Hz)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Magnitud (dB)')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Efecto del pre-énfasis en el espectro')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(OUTPUT / 'pre_emphasis.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.6 Normalización de loudness (LUFS)\n",
    "\n",
    "El estándar **LUFS** (Loudness Units Full Scale, ITU-R BS.1770) es la forma correcta\n",
    "de igualar el volumen percibido entre hablantes. Es mejor que normalizar por pico\n",
    "o por RMS porque incorpora la sensibilidad del oído humano por frecuencia.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Por qué importa para los features**:\n",
    "- Sin normalizar, el hablante más quieto tiene energy_db sistemáticamente más bajo\n",
    "- Esto contamina la línea base relativa (su \"base\" ya incluye el sesgo de nivel)\n",
    "- Con LUFS normalizados, las diferencias de energía reflejan *cambios dinámicos*, no niveles absolutos"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def normalize_loudness(y: np.ndarray, sr: int,\n",
    "                       target_lufs: float = -16.0) -> np.ndarray:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Normaliza la loudness integrada a target_lufs (LUFS).\n",
    "    Usa pyloudnorm que implementa el algoritmo ITU-R BS.1770-4.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    meter  = pyln.Meter(sr)   # crea el medidor para la tasa de muestreo dada\n",
    "    lufs_before = meter.integrated_loudness(y.astype(np.float64))\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not np.isfinite(lufs_before):\n",
    "        print('No se pudo medir LUFS (señal muy corta o silenciosa). Sin cambios.')\n",
    "        return y\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_norm = pyln.normalize.loudness(y.astype(np.float64), lufs_before, target_lufs)\n",
    "    lufs_after = meter.integrated_loudness(y_norm)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Evitar clipping post-normalización\n",
    "    peak = np.abs(y_norm).max()\n",
    "    if peak > 0.99:\n",
    "        y_norm = y_norm / peak * 0.99\n",
    "        print(f'  Peak clipping prevenido: normalizado por pico adicional')\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'Loudness: {lufs_before:.1f} LUFS → {lufs_after:.1f} LUFS  (target: {target_lufs} LUFS)')\n",
    "    return y_norm.astype(np.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_norm = normalize_loudness(y_pe, SR, TARGET_LUFS)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4.7 VAD — Recorte de silencios prolongados\n",
    "\n",
    "Los silencios largos (> 0.5 s) no aportan información y:\n",
    "- Dilatan el análisis temporal\n",
    "- Confunden la estimación de la línea base (frames de silencio tienen features raras)\n",
    "- Reducen el porcentaje útil de audio para la base\n",
    "\n",
    "Usamos un VAD basado en energía: frames con RMS < umbral = silencio.\n",
    "Los silencios menores a `VAD_MIN_SILENCE_S` se conservan (son pausas naturales del habla)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def apply_vad(y: np.ndarray, sr: int,\n",
    "              min_silence_s: float = 0.5,\n",
    "              energy_threshold: float = 0.01,\n",
    "              frame_length: int = 512,\n",
    "              hop_length: int = 256) -> tuple:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Detecta frames de voz y elimina silencios prolongados.\n",
    "    Devuelve (y_vad, df_vad_segments) donde df_vad_segments es la\n",
    "    tabla de segmentos de voz en el audio ORIGINAL (para re-alinear\n",
    "    los timestamps con la diarización).\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    rms        = librosa.feature.rms(y=y, frame_length=frame_length, hop_length=hop_length)[0]\n",
    "    threshold  = rms.max() * energy_threshold\n",
    "    voiced_frames = rms > threshold\n",
    "\n",
    "    min_sil_frames = int(min_silence_s * sr / hop_length)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Suavizar: eliminar baches cortos de silencio (< min_sil_frames)\n",
    "    from scipy.ndimage import binary_closing, binary_opening\n",
    "    voiced_smooth = binary_closing(voiced_frames,\n",
    "                                   structure=np.ones(min_sil_frames))\n",
    "    # Eliminar islas de voz muy cortas (< 0.1s)\n",
    "    voiced_smooth = binary_opening(voiced_smooth,\n",
    "                                   structure=np.ones(max(1, int(0.1 * sr / hop_length))))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Convertir a segmentos en samples del audio original\n",
    "    segments = []\n",
    "    in_voice = False\n",
    "    for i, v in enumerate(voiced_smooth):\n",
    "        t = librosa.frames_to_samples(i, hop_length=hop_length)\n",
    "        if v and not in_voice:\n",
    "            seg_start = t\n",
    "            in_voice  = True\n",
    "        elif not v and in_voice:\n",
    "            segments.append((seg_start, min(t, len(y))))\n",
    "            in_voice = False\n",
    "    if in_voice:\n",
    "        segments.append((seg_start, len(y)))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Concatenar segmentos de voz\n",
    "    chunks = [y[s:e] for s, e in segments]\n",
    "    if not chunks:\n",
    "        print('VAD: sin voz detectada.')\n",
    "        return y, pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_vad = np.concatenate(chunks)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Tabla de segmentos (en tiempo original)\n",
    "    df_vad = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "        [(s/sr, e/sr, (e-s)/sr) for s, e in segments],\n",
    "        columns=['start_orig_s', 'end_orig_s', 'duration_s']\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    removed_s  = (len(y) - len(y_vad)) / sr\n",
    "    print(f'VAD: {len(segments)} segmentos de voz detectados')\n",
    "    print(f'  Silencio eliminado: {removed_s:.1f} s  '\n",
    "          f'({removed_s/len(y)*sr*100:.1f}% del total)')\n",
    "    print(f'  Audio resultante  : {len(y_vad)/sr:.1f} s')\n",
    "\n",
    "    return y_vad.astype(np.float32), df_vad\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "y_vad, df_vad = apply_vad(y_norm, SR, VAD_MIN_SILENCE_S, VAD_ENERGY_THRESH)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualizar\n",
    "t_ax = np.linspace(0, len(y_norm) / SR, len(y_norm))\n",
    "rms_v = librosa.feature.rms(y=y_norm, frame_length=512, hop_length=256)[0]\n",
    "t_rms = librosa.frames_to_time(np.arange(len(rms_v)), sr=SR, hop_length=256)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(16, 6), sharex=True)\n",
    "ax1.plot(t_ax, y_norm, color='steelblue', linewidth=0.3)\n",
    "for _, row in df_vad.iterrows():\n",
    "    ax1.axvspan(row['start_orig_s'], row['end_orig_s'],\n",
    "                color='#4CAF50', alpha=0.25, label='Voz detectada')\n",
    "ax1.set_title('VAD — segmentos de voz detectados (verde)')\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('Amplitud')\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2.fill_between(t_rms, librosa.amplitude_to_db(rms_v, ref=rms_v.max()),\n",
    "                  color='darkorange', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "ax2.axhline(20*np.log10(VAD_ENERGY_THRESH), color='red', linestyle='--',\n",
    "             linewidth=1.5, label='Umbral VAD')\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('RMS (dB)')\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel('Tiempo (s)')\n",
    "ax2.legend(fontsize=8)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(OUTPUT / 'vad.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
